  <bioghist id="aspace_34b7ce2ed84ca79b3ce6c35615054770">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Flower of the Dragon was a community group concerned with Vietnam War veterans based in Santa Rosa, California.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c4ee2fa62d0d6dda05f4294b9e45dfe8">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Clippings about the organization; broadside; publications, mostly United States government; materials from anti-war groups; tape of radio program; reports; article; scrapbook; and photographs, slides, and negatives of unidentified Vietnam scenes.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_2f2e4bccafb930dc2565c4c8cc84bf77">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Flower of the Dragon Records, #7020. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
